issue.body:
Subsquare does not seem to automatically detect or attempt to sign with ones existing governance proxy relationship.  It does appear Subsquare has a field to indicate one's desired proxy account.

When this field is populated with the polkadot address of the proxy account, the following error occurs:

I've verified the proxy relationship in polkadot.js.org, and have used the indicated governance proxy to sign transactions for many years.

Proxy addresses sign transactions on behalf of the proxied address. > > > It seems like this should read _"All your transactions will be submitted on behalf of your address by this proxy address:"_ > > Also the way you phrased it _"You don't have to set a proxy on the settings page if you want to sign a transaction for a proxy address"_ I would say that this way _"You don't have to set a proxy on the settings page if you want your proxy address to sign a transaction for your account address"_ > > I hope this feedback is helpful Sorry, our copywriting have some misleadings. The input address should be the proxied address. For a proxy relationship, with `A-> B`, then A is the proxied account, B is the proxy account. pull_request.title: tweak(fps): Decouple logic time step from render update
pull_request.body:
**Merge with Rebase**

* Relates to #850
* Resolves #279

This change has several commits to fix and improve several aspects in regards to the render frame time in relation to the logic time step.

The frame limiter has been reimplemented with a high accuracy counter for more accurate FPS capping.

The following systems are now decoupled from the render update:
* non-network logic update
* WW3D::Sync
* Scripted camera movement time step
* Drawable time step
* Camera shaker time step
* Camera zoom and rotation time step

There are way more things that could be decoupled but for starters this appears to be good enough and usable.

To control the Logic Time Scale FPS and Render FPS the following default key mapping are added:

| Key mapping | Action |
|-------------|--------|
| CTRL + Numpad+ | Increase Max Render FPS with preset values |
| CTRL + Numpad- | Decrease Max Render FPS with preset values |
| Shift + CTRL + Numpad+ | Increase Logic Time Scale FPS by 5 |
| Shift + CTRL + Numpad- | Decrease Logic Time Scale FPS by 5 |

Changes to the FPS are currently NOT saved to Options.ini and the game still applies its frame rate adjustements in Skirmish, Campaign and similar as usual. By default, the game behaves as originally and this feature is currently entirely opt-in with the key mappings.
